          <h2 style="
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important; 
            ">FBI chief stepping down</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-dec-13-1.jpg" alt="FBI chief stepping down" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">FBI Director Christopher A. Wray says he will <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/11/politics/fbi-director-chris-wray-steps-down/index.html" target="_blank">resign</a> in January 2025, at the end of President Biden's term. Wray's resignation follows announcement efforts by Trump and GOP leaders, including <a href="https://eu.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/elections/2024/12/09/sen-chuck-grassley-fbi-director-christopher-wray/76865407007/" target="_blank">Senator Chuck Grassley</a>, to push him out. Trump appointed Wray in 2017, but their relationship has soured since then, particularly concerning Wray's involvement in <a href="https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/elections/2024/12/11/fbi-director-christopher-wray-fought-trump/76926283007/" target="_blank">investigations</a> related to Trump and his invasion of Mar-a-Lago.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">After the announcement, Trump expressed that the resignation would end the weaponization of the U.S. Department of Justice. Their relationship has been turbulent, especially after Trump <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/20180202-trump-accuses-justice-dept-fbi-pro-democrat-bias" target="_blank">accused</a> the FBI of bias post-presidency. By resigning, Wray could avoid being fired and allow the FBI to function smoothly until a new director is appointed. During his speech, Wray insisted that the FBI cannot change its commitment to doing the right thing, the right way, every time. Praise and harsh criticism have been showered on Wray since the announcement.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Human rights at FIFA</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-dec-13-2.jpg" alt="Human rights at FIFA" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)">Saudi Arabia is now the <a href="https://apnews.com/article/fifa-world-cup-2030-2034-saudi-arabia-spain-portugal-945f8d7bf332553de0726901d096b956" target="_blank">official</a> 2034 FIFA World Cup host. They were the only candidate, and their bid automatically made them the host. This was followed by applause from 200 FIFA member federations via a virtual meeting. FIFA President Gianni Infantino <a href="https://inside.fifa.com/about-fifa/president/news/world-cup-2030-morocco-portugal-spain-2034-saudi-unity-infantino" target="_blank">welcomed</a> the decision and believed the World Cup could bring about positive social change and open the world to Saudi Arabia's welcoming elements.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)">
          <a href="https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2024/11/global-fifa-should-halt-process-for-2034-world-cup-bid-and-demand-credible-human-rights-strategy-for-2030/" target="_blank">Human rights groups</a> are not pleased with the choice and warn that Saudi Arabia’s labor conditions and human rights record could be at risk of worsening. They could be on par with the <a href="https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/qatar-world-cup-2022-deaths-b2244081.html" target="_blank">controversies</a> surrounding Qatar’s 2022 World Cup. The critics argue that FIFA has not adequately ensured protections for <a href="https://sportandrightsalliance.org/award-of-2034-mens-world-cup-to-saudi-arabia-risks-lives-and-exposes-fifas-empty-human-rights-commitments/" target="_blank">migrant workers</a> involved in the massive infrastructure projects needed for the tournament. Some others present that this judgment from the West should be reconsidered and cited that much of the Qatar World Cup criticism was rooted in racism and hypocrisy, including the <a href="https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63687412#:~:text=Fifa%20president%20Gianni%20Infantino%20has,of%20Qatar%20and%20the%20tournament." target="_blank">FIFA president</a> himself.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    
